This paper discusses a system for distributing large data sets in a scalable and cost-effective manner. The system is specifically designed for use in the machine learning community, which suggests that it is likely to fall under the categories of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), or Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). Given the focus on data distribution and peer-to-peer networking, cs.DC and cs.NI seem like the most likely categories, followed by cs.IR and cs.LG. The paper does not appear to focus on cryptography or security, so cs.CR is less likely.
